{{Portal|Anglicanism}}'''Brownlow Thomas Atlay''' (b 10 June 1832 [[Great Casterton]]; d. 16 September 1912 [[Ealing]])<ref>[http://website.lineone.net/~hstjw/p3.htm#i1725 Line One]</ref>  was [[Archdeacon of Calcutta]] from 1883 until 1888.<ref>[[John Venn]], [[John Archibald Venn]], ''[[Alumni Cantabrigienses|Alumni Cantabrigienses: A Biographical List of All Known Students, Graduates and Holders of Office at the University of Cambridge, from the Earliest Times to 1900]]'', Pt2 Vol 1 p96</ref>

