According to the [[Book of Mormon]], '''King Noah''' was a wicked monarch best known for burning the prophet [[Abinadi]] at the stake. King Noah, described in the [[Book of Mosiah]], is said to have presided over a wicked kingdom guided by false [[priest]]s.  Noah succeeds his father [[Zeniff]], and is succeeded by his son [[Limhi]].

